Chaos erupts at the Pan Africa Parliament today where new a leadership was expected to be elected. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Chaotic scenes playing out once again at the Pan African Parliament. This as leadership elections were due to get underway on Tuesday afternoon. READ: Pan-African Parliament expected to elect new leadership Chaos erupted on Monday as some MPs argued against rotational leadership. The southern African caucus is demanding reform, wanting the position to be on a rotational basis.